defs.docs: Simple getopt alternative.

defs.name: Options
defs.docs: A description of the options that a program can handle.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a blank set of options.

defs.name: parsing_style
defs.docs: Set the parsing style.

defs.name: long_only
defs.docs: Set or clear "long options only" mode.

defs.name: opt
defs.value: fn (&mut self, short_name: &str, long_name: &str, desc: &str, hint: &str, hasarg: HasArg, occur: Occur) -> &mut Options
defs.docs: Create a generic option group, stating all parameters explicitly.

defs.name: optflag
defs.value: fn (&mut self, short_name: &str, long_name: &str, desc: &str) -> &mut Options
defs.docs: Create a long option that is optional and does not take an argument.

defs.name: optflagmulti
defs.value: fn (&mut self, short_name: &str, long_name: &str, desc: &str) -> &mut Options
defs.docs:
Create a long option that can occur more than once and does not
 take an argument.

defs.name: optflagopt
defs.value: fn (&mut self, short_name: &str, long_name: &str, desc: &str, hint: &str) -> &mut Options
defs.docs: Create a long option that is optional and takes an optional argument.

defs.name: optmulti
defs.value: fn (&mut self, short_name: &str, long_name: &str, desc: &str, hint: &str) -> &mut Options
defs.docs:
Create a long option that is optional, takes an argument, and may occur
 multiple times.

defs.name: optopt
defs.value: fn (&mut self, short_name: &str, long_name: &str, desc: &str, hint: &str) -> &mut Options
defs.docs: Create a long option that is optional and takes an argument.

defs.name: reqopt
defs.value: fn (&mut self, short_name: &str, long_name: &str, desc: &str, hint: &str) -> &mut Options
defs.docs: Create a long option that is required and takes an argument.

defs.name: parse
defs.docs: Parse command line arguments according to the provided options.

defs.name: short_usage
defs.docs: Derive a short one-line usage summary from a set of long options.

defs.name: usage
defs.docs: Derive a formatted message from a set of options.

defs.name: usage_with_format
defs.docs:
Derive a custom formatted message from a set of options. The formatted options provided to
 a closure as an iterator.

defs.name: FloatingFrees
defs.docs: Flags and "free" arguments can be freely inter-mixed.

defs.name: StopAtFirstFree
defs.docs:
As soon as a "free" argument (i.e. non-flag) is encountered, stop
 considering any remaining arguments as flags.

defs.name: ParsingStyle
defs.docs: What parsing style to use when parsing arguments.

defs.name: Yes
defs.docs: The option requires an argument.

defs.name: No
defs.docs: The option takes no argument.

defs.name: Maybe
defs.docs: The option argument is optional.

defs.name: HasArg
defs.docs: Describes whether an option has an argument.

defs.name: Req
defs.docs: The option occurs once.

defs.name: Optional
defs.docs: The option occurs at most once.

defs.name: Multi
defs.docs: The option occurs zero or more times.

defs.name: Occur
defs.docs: Describes how often an option may occur.

defs.name: Matches
defs.docs:
The result of checking command line arguments. Contains a vector
 of matches and a vector of free strings.

defs.name: free
defs.docs: Free string fragments

defs.name: ArgumentMissing
defs.docs: The option requires an argument but none was passed.

defs.name: UnrecognizedOption
defs.docs: The passed option is not declared among the possible options.

defs.name: OptionMissing
defs.docs: A required option is not present.

defs.name: OptionDuplicated
defs.docs: A single occurrence option is being used multiple times.

defs.name: UnexpectedArgument
defs.docs: There's an argument being passed to a non-argument option.

defs.name: Fail
defs.docs:
The type returned when the command line does not conform to the
 expected format. Use the `Debug` implementation to output detailed
 information.

defs.name: Result
defs.docs: The result of parsing a command line with a set of options.

defs.name: opt_defined
defs.docs: Returns true if an option was defined

defs.name: opt_present
defs.docs: Returns true if an option was matched.

defs.name: opt_count
defs.docs: Returns the number of times an option was matched.

defs.name: opts_present
defs.docs: Returns true if any of several options were matched.

defs.name: opts_str
defs.docs: Returns the string argument supplied to one of several matching options or `None`.

defs.name: opt_strs
defs.docs:
Returns a vector of the arguments provided to all matches of the given
 option.

defs.name: opt_str
defs.docs: Returns the string argument supplied to a matching option or `None`.

defs.name: opt_default
defs.docs: Returns the matching string, a default, or `None`.

defs.name: opt_get
defs.docs: Returns some matching value or `None`.

defs.name: opt_get_default
defs.value: fn <T> (&self, nm: &str, def: T) -> result::Result<T, T::Err>
defs.docs: Returns a matching value or default.
